
// How to disable geo-location in Mozilla Firefox
1. open firefox and type "about:config"
2. Then search for "geo.enabled". Double click to change the boolean value to "false"
3. In case the new setting is not saved, you need to clear the "Catche"
    3.1. How to clear Catche?
         a. Firefox -> Preference -> Advanced -> Network -> Catched Web Content (click "Clear Now")
